30-character summary:
Quick Git commit with timestamp

---
syntax: bash
tags: [bash, personal, git, commit]
version: 1.0.0
---

NAME
    git-now - Quickly commit all changes with a timestamped message

SYNOPSIS
    git now [options] [<message>]

DESCRIPTION
    git-now is a custom Git command that allows users to quickly commit all changes in the working directory with a timestamped commit message. If no message is provided, it uses a default message.

OPTIONS
    -h, --help      Show help information
    -v, --version   Show version information
    -a, --all       Stage all changes, including untracked files
    -f, --force     Commit even if there are no changes
    -p, --push      Push the commit immediately after committing

USAGE
    Run git-now in a Git repository to quickly commit changes with a timestamped message.

EXAMPLES
    git now
    git now "Quick fix"
    git now -a "Add new feature"
    git now -p "Update documentation"

OUTPUT
    Confirmation of the commit, including the commit hash and message.
